1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 4144 By: Manger of the House
5 and
6 Hamilton of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Open Records Act;
amending 51 O.S. 2021, Section 24A.8, as amended by
11 Section 1, Chapter 12, O.S.L. 2022 (51 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 24A.8), which relates to law
12 enforcement records; eliminating reference to a
chronological list of incidents; requiring law
13 enforcement agencies to make all arrest and incident
reports available for public inspection; and
14 providing an effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 51 O.S. 2021, Section 24A.8, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 12, O.S.L. 2022 (51 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 24A.8), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 24A.8. A. Law enforcement agencies shall make
22 available for public inspection and copying, if kept, the following
23 records:
24
HB4144 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 1. An arrestee description, including the name, date of birth,
2 address, race, sex, physical description, and occupation of the
3 arrestee;
4 2. Facts concerning the arrest, including the cause of arrest
5 and the name of the arresting officer;
6 3. A chronological list of all incidents All arrest and
7 incident reports, including but not limited to, initial offense
8 report information showing the offense, date, time, general
9 location, officer, and a brief summary of what occurred;
10 4. Radio logs, including a chronological listing of the calls
11 dispatched;
12 5. Conviction information, including the name of any person
13 convicted of a criminal offense;
14 6. Disposition of all warrants, including orders signed by a
15 judge of any court commanding a law enforcement officer to arrest a
16 particular person;
17 7. A crime summary, including an agency summary of crimes
18 reported and public calls for service by classification or nature
19 and number;
20 8. Jail registers, including jail blotter data or jail booking
21 information recorded on persons at the time of incarceration showing
22 the name of each prisoner with the date and cause of commitment, the
23 authority committing the prisoner, whether committed for a criminal
